I am trying to troubleshoot my KSP but not sure what do I look for to find out which mod is causing the error. It loads the game gets to the main screen and I am not able to select any of menu.

On 12/28/2021 at 10:45 PM, commanderbunbun said:

I am trying to troubleshoot my KSP but not sure what do I look for to find out which mod is causing the error. It loads the game gets to the main screen and I am not able to select any of menu.

Player.log

KSP.log

Your first problem is that you have multiple versions of ModuleManager installed.  Delete all but the latest.

From the log, you are missing a whole bunch of DLLs, this is a partial list: 

ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: EVEManager, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: Utils, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: KSPDev_Utils.2.6-KAS, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: KSPDev_Utils.2.4, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: KSPDev_Utils.2.6-EVS, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: SCANsat.Unity, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: KSPe.Light.KAX, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: 000_AT_Utils, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: 001_AnisotropicPartResizer, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: CC.UI, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: CC.UI, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 

ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: KSPUtil, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 
ADDON BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: KSPUtil, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null 

 BINDER: Cannot resolve assembly: ToadicusTools, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null

There's more, I just stopped at this point

I don't know how you installed this, but I am certain you didn't use CKAN.

I suggest you redo your install using CKAN to do as many of the mods as you can
